  "texts": [
    "Baum and her colleagues were interested in finding out why people with dementia cope better at all kinds of tasks when they are in environments that accommodate their distinctive needs and supply for their deficits (for a recent survey of this work, see Bass et al., 2017).",
    "The observation is a familiar one.",
    "Many of us have watched older relatives undergoing cognitive decline struggle in unfamiliar environments while coping fluently at home.",
    "On the views set out above, the source of this struggle can be understood as a kind of cognitive disintegration, in which the biological brain is no longer able to constrain its information processing (2025) 205:47 to the kind of holistic consistency we expect of unimpaired persons.",
    "We might then say that the props and supports of a familiar or well-designed environment mitigate against these deficits, restoring the order characteristic of ordinary cognition (see Drayson & Clark, 2018)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Baum and her colleagues were interested in finding out why people with dementia cope better at all kinds of tasks when they are in environments that accommodate their distinctive needs and supply for their deficits (for a recent survey of this work, see Bass et al., 2017).",
